## Loading required package: fma
## Loading required package: expsmooth
data <- read.csv(file='./data/qty_promotion.csv')
series <- ts(data, start=1, end=113 + 4/7, frequency=7)
train <- window(series[,1], start=1, end=105 + 1/7 ,frequency=7)
test <- window(series[,1], start=105 + 2/7, end=113 + 4/7, frequency = 7)
promo_train <-  window(series[,2], start=1, end=105 + 1/7 ,frequency=7)
#FIT
arima_fit <- auto.arima(train, approximation=FALSE , stepwise=FALSE)
#Accuracy, residuals, modelo
accuracy(arima_fit)
##                      ME     RMSE      MAE       MPE     MAPE     MASE
## Training set -0.6079082 45.61764 33.92293 -5.309262 18.38931 0.711292
##                    ACF1
## Training set 0.00195817
checkresiduals(arima_fit)

## 
##  Ljung-Box test
## 
## data:  Residuals from ARIMA(0,0,3)(0,1,1)[7] with drift

arima_fit
## Series: train 
## ARIMA(0,0,3)(0,1,1)[7] with drift

##          ma1     ma2     ma3     sma1    drift

## sigma^2 estimated as 2116:  log likelihood=-3798.48

plot_start = 0
plot_end = 30
autoplot(ts(train[plot_start:plot_end]), series='train') +
  autolayer(ts(fitted(arima_fit)[plot_start:plot_end]),  series="fitted") +
  xlab("day") +
  ylab("quantity") +
  ggtitle("Comparaçao de valores de treino com fitted") +
  guides(colour=guide_legend(title="Legend"))

#Fit sem stepwise e aproximation
result_arima <- forecast(arima_fit,h = 59)
plot_start = 0
plot_end = 59
autoplot(ts(test[plot_start:plot_end]), series='treino') +
  autolayer(ts(result_arima$mean[plot_start:plot_end]),  series="Forecasted") +
  xlab("day") +
  ylab("Value") +
  ggtitle("Comparacão de valores forecasted e testes") +
  guides(colour=guide_legend(title="Legenda"))

#accuracy de forecasted com treino
accuracy(result_arima,test)

#residuos em tabela
#View dos valores de teste, forecasted e diferenças
test_matrix = as.matrix(test)
forecasted_matrix = as.matrix(result_arima$mean)
difference_test <- test_matrix - forecasted_matrix

test_table_difference = data.frame( test_matrix, forecasted_matrix, difference_test)

names(test_table_difference)[1] <- "teste"
names(test_table_difference)[2] <- "forecasted"
names(test_table_difference)[3] <- "diferença"

view(test_table_difference)
#residuos em tabela
